# B-Tree Implementation in C++

## Overview

This project implements a B-Tree data structure in C++. A B-Tree is a self-balancing search tree commonly used in databases and file systems. It supports efficient insertion, searching, and traversal operations.

## Features

* Create a B-Tree with a specified minimum degree.
* Insert keys into the B-Tree.
* Search for keys in the B-Tree.
* Traverse and display all keys in sorted order.

## Files

* `btree.cpp` – Source code for the B-Tree implementation.

## Compilation

Using g++:

```bash
g++ btree.cpp -o btree
```

For Windows (PowerShell):

```powershell
g++ btree.cpp -o btree.exe
```

## Execution

Linux/macOS:

```bash
./btree
```

Windows (PowerShell):

```powershell
.\btree.exe
```

## Sample Output

```text
Traversal of B-Tree:
5 6 7 10 12 17 20 30
Key 12 found
```

## Operations Supported

### Insert

Adds a new key while maintaining B-Tree properties.

### Search

Checks whether a key exists in the tree.

### Traverse

Prints all keys in sorted order.

## Time Complexity

| Operation | Complexity |
| --------- | ---------- |
| Search    | O(log n)   |
| Insert    | O(log n)   |
| Traverse  | O(n)       |

